PREP: 10 minutes
COOK: 1 hour
YIELD: 1 tray

INGREDIENTS:
1 lb pecan halves
1 egg white
1 tbs water
1 cup white sugar
1 tsp cinamon

DIRECTIONS:
Preheat oven to 250&deg;F
Whisk egg white and watter for about 20 seconds, until foamy.
In a large bowl, mix pecans with egg white mixture.
Add sugar and cinnamon. Mix until everything is evenly distributed.
Pour pecans onto parchment lined baking sheet and arrange into a relatively flat layer.
Bake for 1 hour, tossing every 15 minutes.

